          "Flipkart users may soon get food deliveries via ONDC\n\n\n\nBy \xa0 ONDC\n\nJun 4, 2024\n\nUpdated: Jun 4, 2024\n\n1 min read\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nBlog\n\nNews\n\nFlipkart users may soon get food deliveries via ONDC\n\nPublication - BusinessLine\n\nEdition - Online\n\nThe government-backed Open Network for Digital Commerce (ONDC) is in advanced discussions with Flipkart as the e-commerce major may soon foray into food and beverages (F&B) category on the platform.\n\nIt could mean that users may soon be able to order from a wide range of restaurants and fast-food outlets.\n\nWhile the food and beverage is just the starting point, logistics is to soon follow, promising good prices and immediate responses. Despite advanced stages of integration with ONDC, Flipkart’s logistics subsidiary Ekart has not been very active. The company plans to operate on the buyer-side of ONDC, meaning shoppers can order food while searching for fashion and apparel on Flipkart.\n\nPlease click on the link below:\n\nFlipkart users may soon get food deliveries via ONDCONDC in talks with Flipkart and Amazon for food and beverage expansion, promising wide range, good prices, and quick deliveries.BusinessLineJyoti Banthia\n\nNews\n\nKeep reading\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC is making e-commerce space democratised for all players\n\nNews\n\na year ago · 2 min read\n\nTransactions in ONDC seeing growth across the board\n\nNews\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nTomato Price Rise: NCCF To Sell Subsidised Tomatoes On ONDC In Delhi\n\nNews\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
