          "Ola eyes grocery and fashion foray on ONDC\n\n\n\nBy \xa0 ONDC\n\nApr 15, 2024\n\nUpdated: Apr 15, 2024\n\n1 min read\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nBlog\n\nNews\n\nOla eyes grocery and fashion foray on ONDC\n\nPublication - Economic Times\n\nEdition - Online\n\nRide-hailing company Ola will soon offer its customers the option to shop for groceries and fashion and apparel on Open Network for Digital Commerce (ONDC) via its app, broadening the suite of e-commerce offerings to its 75 million monthly active users.\n\nCurrently, customers can only order food and beverages on ONDC through the Ola app.\n\nPlease click on the link below:\n\nOla eyes grocery and fashion foray on ONDCOla expands e-commerce via ONDC, adding groceries and fashion. Uber may use ONDC for diversification. Ola sees profitability with Rs 250 crore Ebitda in FY23, revenue grows 58%, loss reduces 65%.Economic TimesSuraksha P\n\nNews\n\nKeep reading\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC is making e-commerce space democratised for all players\n\nNews\n\na year ago · 2 min read\n\nTransactions in ONDC seeing growth across the board\n\nNews\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nTomato Price Rise: NCCF To Sell Subsidised Tomatoes On ONDC In Delhi\n\nNews\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
