          "VP-Logistics\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nCareer\n\nVP-Logistics\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are rewriting the rules of the ecommerce industry in India and seeking an experienced professional to program manage all projects and new initiatives driven from the COO office. If you thrive in a fast-paced, innovative environment, apply now and be a part of our groundbreaking journey.\n\nRoles and Responsibilities\n\nStrategy: Establish a clear vision for the ONDC logistics ecosystem, ensuring alignment with overall network goals and emphasizing scalability and efficiency. Define and implement strategies for onboarding various logistics service providers (LSPs) across different service levels (hyperlocal, regional, national, B2B, etc.), independent of other products on the network. Develop a clear value proposition for Logistics on ONDC.\n\nEcosystem Building: Forge a robust, efficient population-scale logistics ecosystem on the network to facilitate seamless operations for Buyer/Seller NPs, offering diverse solutions for various categories.\n\nBuilding & Owning Relationships: Liaise with Logistics Service Providers (LSP), industry bodies/confederations, and other key stakeholders to support the ever-expanding product categories and use cases on the network.\n\nStakeholder Collaboration: Collaborate with internal teams (technology, network expansion, operations) and external stakeholders (LSPs) to ensure a cohesive and integrated logistics experience on the network.\n\nProgram/Project Management: Support initiatives across the ONDC organization, ensuring timely onboarding of LSPs.\n\nOperational Excellence: Orchestrate a logistics network with optimum cost structures, service quality, and offerings in line with ONDC's growth ambitions.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nMaster's degree in Business Administration (MBA) or equivalent qualification.\n\nExtensive background in logistics and supply chain management, particularly focused on ecommerce operations.\n\nProven track record of successfully leading and managing complex logistics networks.\n\nPassion for digital commerce, logistics, and technology, with a history of solving large-scale problems and effectively leading and managing teams.\n\nIn-depth knowledge of the logistics and supply chain landscape in the country, including familiarity with the latest trends and technologies.\n\nExceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with a talent for negotiation and relationship-building.\n\nFamiliarity with the Indian digital commerce landscape, with particular experience on leading ecommerce/hyperlocal platforms in logistics, strategy, consulting, or related fields considered advantageous.\n\nPreference for candidates with experience in high-growth operations, technology, or startups.\n\nApply Now\n\nJobs\n\nProduct Manager\n\nBusiness Analyst\n\nPolicy Manager\n\nApply For\n\nSame as Permanent Address\n\nExperience *\n\nProfile Photo *\n\nResume *\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
