          "Architect - Open Stack\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nCareer\n\nArchitect - Open Stack\n\nJob Description\n\nWe're seeking an adept and enthusiastic Architect to join our team. As part of this role, you'll take charge of refining and expanding the ONDC Developer Guide, ensuring it caters to diverse business scenarios. Collaboration will be key as you closely engage with the ONDC tech team, participant communities, and stakeholders to facilitate the uptake and effective application of the ONDC specifications. Additionally, you'll contribute to the development of tools and features aimed at enhancing adoption rates.\n\nRoles and Responsibilities\n\nEnhance ONDC specification to support different business use cases, for products & services, in domains like agriculture, mobility, travel & tourism, etc.;\n\nDrafting ONDC specifications and its elements OpenAPI standards along with beckn protocol\n\nSupport ONDC Tech Team in enhancing specifications in different areas, such as Payments & Settlements, Ratings, Inter-city logistics, and drive adoption of the protocols by the stakeholders, etc.;\n\nBuild utilities for optimal harmonisation between different buyers & sellers on the network;\n\nWork with the participant community to improve experience and simplify the implementation of ONDC specification;\n\nCreate POCs for ecosystems to demonstrate usage of the specification for specific business domains;\n\nContribute to the ONDC specs on Github\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nAt least 4-6 years of hands-on experience in developing technologies for protocols – Open API, RESTful APIs, JSON;\n\nExcellent understanding of adapting protocols for different business domains e.g. adaptations required for retail e-commerce, mobility, agriculture;\n\nWorking knowledge of one or more of the following programming languages such as Java, Nodejs, Python, Golang, etc.;\n\nAPI development tools such as Swagger, source code versioning system such as Github;\n\nEngineering degree required, with minimum qualification of BE / BTech / MTech / MCA\n\nProficiency in developing with open APIs and creating transaction-level contracts.\n\nApply Now\n\nJobs\n\nProduct Manager\n\nBusiness Analyst\n\nVP-Logistics\n\nApply For\n\nSame as Permanent Address\n\nExperience *\n\nProfile Photo *\n\nResume *\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
