          "ONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nGoogle Partners with ONDC for 'Build for Bharat' Hackathon\n\n\n\nBy \xa0 ONDC\n\nSep 20, 2023\n\nUpdated: Sep 20, 2023\n\n2 min read\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nBlog\n\nONDC\n\nGoogle Partners with ONDC for 'Build for Bharat' Hackathon\n\nThe ONDC is proud to announce that Google Cloud is partnering with ONDC for the 'Build for Bharat' nationwide hackathon. This exciting partnership aims to tackle challenges in the digital commerce landscape and foster innovation to deliver practical solutions.\n\nWhat is 'Build for Bharat'?\n\nThe 'Build for Bharat' hackathon provides a dynamic platform where startups and developers can harness their skills and creativity to drive innovation within the ONDC network. Our goal is to establish an open ecosystem that continually nurtures innovation.\n\nWho Can Participate?\n\nThe hackathon is for a diverse range of participants, including school students, college students, developers (both individuals and organisations), and startups, with the target of reaching over 1,00,000 participants.\n\nMentorship and Support by Google\n\nIn addition to the hackathon itself, Google will provide invaluable mentorship and support to participants. This support includes webinars, online masterclasses, doubt-solving sessions, and access to online community channels. It's an opportunity for participants to learn from industry experts and refine their skills.\n\nIt is great to see that within just four days of launching, the hackathon has received an overwhelming response, with over 1,000 enrollments for problem statement registration. This remarkable start is a testament to the enthusiasm and commitment of our community.\n\nThe 'Build for Bharat' hackathon is a significant step forward in ONDC's mission to transform digital commerce in India. We look forward to witnessing the innovative solutions that will emerge from this collaboration between ONDC and Google.\n\nCome and Participate in this transformatory opportunity to Build for Bharat\n\nTo know more about the “Build for Bharat” hackathon you can visit:\n\nBuild For Bharat Hackathon | ONDC | Google Cloud | Hack2skillgoogle cloud\n\nSocial Media Links:\n\nHack to Skill\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/hack2skill/\n\nONDC\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/100076520217598/videos/ondc-is-teaming-up-with-google-cloud-to-democratize-digital-commerce-with-the-bu/981347809838863/\n\nhttps://x.com/ONDC_Official/status/1699785979421450270?s=20\n\nGoogle India\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/GoogleCloudIN\n\nhttps://x.com/GoogleIndia/status/1702296422065029580?s=20\n\nONDC\n\nKeep reading\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC Academy : Your guide to e-commerce enabled by the ONDC Network\n\nONDC Academy\n\nONDC\n\nDigital\n\n2 years ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC is now Beta testing in Meerut!\n\nBusiness\n\nONDC\n\n2 years ago · 2 min read\n\nONDC Incentive Program for Bengaluru Plus:  Inviting all interested participants starting 16th December.\n\nBusiness\n\nONDC\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nPowered By\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
