          "Media Coverage - ONDC Beta Launch in Bengaluru\n\n\n\nBy \xa0 Team ONDC\n\nOct 1, 2022\n\nUpdated: Oct 1, 2022\n\n2 min read\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHome\n\nBlog\n\nNews\n\nMedia Coverage - ONDC Beta Launch in Bengaluru\n\nONDC starts beta testing with consumers in 16 pin codes of BengaluruThe objective of the beta test is to allow consumers to experience the network for the first time and gather feedback which will help further refine the network before a pan-India roll-out.Economic TimesSuraksha P\n\nBengaluru consumers to experience, shape ONDC’s new e-commerce revolutionIn a significant milestone, Open Network for Digital Commerce (ONDC), an initiative of the Department of Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT), Ministry of Commerce, Government of India will open its network to consumers in 16 pin codes spread across Bengaluru.Hindustan Times\n\nONDC begins beta testing in Bengaluru today — more on e-commerce glasnostTo begin with, orders can be placed in two categories — restaurants and groceries — via buyer applications participating in the ONDC network.CNBCTV18\n\nONDC To Begin Beta Testing In Bengaluru On FridayBeta testing of the Government’s revolutionary Open Network For Digital Commerce to begin from tomorrow, said Minister of Commerce and Industry Piyush Goyal , , ONDC, piyush goyal, Minister of Commerce and Industry, launch, Beta Testing, bengaluruBW BusinessworldBW Online Bureau\n\nONDC announces launch of Beta Test phase in BengaluruONDC, the open network for ecommerce, will be available across 16 pin codes in Bengaluru with a focus on hyperlocal businesses, including kirana, grocery stores, brand stores, and restaurants.YourStoryTeam YS\n\nNews\n\nKeep reading\n\na year ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC Academy : Your guide to e-commerce enabled by the ONDC Network\n\nONDC Academy\n\nONDC\n\nDigital\n\n2 years ago · 1 min read\n\nONDC is now Beta testing in Meerut!\n\nBusiness\n\nONDC\n\n2 years ago · 2 min read\n\nONDC Incentive Program for Bengaluru Plus:  Inviting all interested participants starting 16th December.\n\nBusiness\n\nONDC\n\nONDC Participant Portal\n\nBegin and efficiently manage your journey on ONDC Network\n\nUnderstand and select your role(s)\n\nTrack, manage and troubleshoot your integration\n\nDiscover and collaborate with others\n\nStay informed on network developments and announcements\n\nNo results for your search, please try with something else.",
